# barbergo — always follow

Authoritative details: `docs/project-rules.md`. Apply on every task in this repo.

## Semi-autonomous workflow

- Continue with sensible defaults; do not stop for unnecessary questions.
- Only ask the user when: security-sensitive actions, destructive ops, unclear major architecture, materially different tech choices, credentials/API keys/accounts needed, or library choices that strongly affect future architecture.
- For small UI, naming, folders, or details: pick a reasonable default, document it briefly, keep going.
- Prefer iterative MVP progress and high momentum.

## Notifications (required, from project root)

Pause for required user input:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/notify-custom.ps1 "User input required"
```

Major task completed (prefer contextual message):

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/notify-custom.ps1 "Task description"
```

Otherwise:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/notify-done.ps1
```

Do not skip. Examples: `"Expo setup completed"`, `"Navigation implemented"`, `"Backend endpoints completed"`.

## Architecture & philosophy

- **Mobile:** Expo, TypeScript, Expo Router, NativeWind | **Backend:** Spring Boot, PostgreSQL
- Simple MVP; beginner-friendly; avoid paid APIs unless requested; reusable components; clean folders
- Ship working MVP fast; concise explanations; explain important decisions **after** implementation, not before blocking

## Workflow

- Small steps; mock data before heavy backend; update docs when setup/behavior changes
